svg.text: RACIAL MAKEUP OF N.J.S SPECIALIZED SCHOOLS

text.tspan: There are now 21 stand-alone high schools called magnet schools, career
academies and high tech high schools across the state designed for high-
achieving students. The schools are run by the county vo-tech districts and most
require students to take admissions exams and undergo interviews to get admitted to
the highly-selective programs. An analysis of state enrollment data from 2015-2016
shows white and Asian students make up large parts of the student bodies at many of
the schools. The data also shows black and Hispanic students are underrepresented
at many of the schools, when compared to the overall public school populations in
their counties. Hover over the pie charts to view percentages.
